There is something on life's journey that I call "Life." If we go on about our lives and not question the life we are leading, then, indeed, we are on the wrong path. I was on that path for many years. I questioned if what I went through was "normal" to happen. I questioned if I could overcome it. I had a counselor and I talked to many people until I had a great answer on questions, then, to the question, "are you happy." I am fortunate to have been blessed with a job that pays for and supports an awesome, loving family. My mother and grandparents were wonderful, loving, caring, and supportive parents. In 1983, I married to the most wonderful, loving, caring, and supportive woman, Ms. Denise M. Smith. It had been a year and a half since I have seen my mother when she was hit head-on with a tractor trailer 12 years ago. That tragic day has been more than challenging. The day my mother fell and hit her head with a tractor trailer, it was my son's birthday. The day she passed, my son's 13th birthday came, so now he is a teenager. The day my father died was the day my son graduated from high school, one day before my mother's death. I knew what to expect when I got home from work on Wednesday, October 17th, 2007. It was my mother's 51st birthday.
